            <fr:number>5.2.6</fr:number>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The functor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {s}\colon \operatorname {C}^+(S_\bullet )\to \operatorname {C}^+(S)]]></fr:tex> sends acyclic complexes to acyclic complexes.
    It thus trivially derives to
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       \mathrm {s}\colon  \mathrm {D}^+(S_\bullet )       \to  \mathrm {D}^+(S).     ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is an injective sheaf on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_\bullet ]]></fr:tex>, then the chain complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {s} F]]></fr:tex> is a resolution of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon _*F]]></fr:tex>.
    We thus obtain an isomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R}\varepsilon _*\xrightarrow {\sim }\mathrm {s}]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.4.2" href="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.4.2.xml" taxon="Equation" number="5.2.4.2" /> becomes

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2362</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-5.2.6.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-5.2.6.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>5.2.6.1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \mathrm {R} a_*         = \mathrm {s}\mathrm {R}{a_\bullet }_*       \tag{5.2.6.1}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
